snippet: The home improvement retailer, the target of a cyberattack affecting as many as 56 million customers, beat analysts’ expectations with $1.5 billion in net earnings.
abstract: Home Depot, target of a cyberattack affecting as many as 56 million customers, beats analysts’ expectations with $1.5 billion profit in third-quarter, or $1.15 per share, compared with $1.4 billion, or 95 cents per share, in year-ago quarter; revenue rose 5.4 percent to $20.5 billion.
lead_paragraph: The home improvement retailer, the target of a cyberattack affecting as many as 56 million customers, beat analysts’ expectations with $1.5 billion in net earnings.

headline.main: Home Depot Posts a Strong 3rd Quarter Despite a Data Breach Disclosure
headline.print_headline: Home Depot Posts a Strong 3rd Quarter Despite a Data Breach Disclosure
